concepts.label: entity
concepts.comment: Anything that exists or has existed or will exist

concepts.label: continuant
concepts.comment: An entity that persists, endures, or continues to exist through time

concepts.label: occurrent
concepts.comment: An entity that has temporal parts and happens, occurs, or unfolds

concepts.label: independent continuant
concepts.comment: A continuant that is a bearer of qualities and roles

concepts.label: specifically dependent continuant
concepts.comment: A continuant that inheres in or is borne by other entities

concepts.label: quality
concepts.comment: A specifically dependent continuant that is exhibited by an entity

concepts.label: role
concepts.comment: A realizable entity that exists because the bearer is in some special context

concepts.label: realizable entity
concepts.comment: A specifically dependent continuant that can be realized in processes

concepts.label: disposition
concepts.comment: A realizable entity that tends to cause certain outcomes under certain conditions

concepts.label: function
concepts.comment: A disposition that exists in virtue of the bearer's physical make-up

concepts.label: process
concepts.comment: An occurrent that has temporal proper parts and unfolds itself in time

concepts.label: temporal region
concepts.comment: An occurrent over which processes can unfold
